main event: An unidentified object was observed by military personnel in the Pacific Ocean on October 3, 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed moving from 3-5 degrees elevation to 6-10 degrees elevation in a slight 15 degree arc in azimuth.
The object apparently dived toward the sea or merged with one of Jupiter's moons.
The report includes possible explanations such as a satellite, balloon, or aircraft, but states that the data was insufficient for a conclusive evaluation.
